¶¶

01:13.908 --> 01:16.542
boyfriend?
What boyfriend?

01:16.544 --> 01:19.344
Oh, no, I can't believe
Charles passed.

01:19.346 --> 01:22.414
Oh, I'm so sorry.

01:28.189 --> 01:31.190
I can't speak Chinese,

01:31.192 --> 01:34.193
but I can tell from your tone
that you're doing okay.

01:34.195 --> 01:36.361
Wait. You knew she had
a boyfriend?

01:36.363 --> 01:37.863
I introduced them.

01:37.865 --> 01:39.932
Charles and Marvin use to work
for the same dental practice.

01:39.934 --> 01:42.968
He was
Marvin's dental mentor.

01:42.970 --> 01:44.436
His "dentor".

01:44.438 --> 01:46.538
Dentor. That's funny.

01:46.540 --> 01:48.540
Wait. So, you didn't know
she had a boyfriend?

01:48.542 --> 01:49.808
No.

01:49.810 --> 01:51.977
But it does explain
some things.

01:51.979 --> 01:53.712
[ Door closes ]

01:53.714 --> 01:56.248
Since when do you stay out
so late?

01:56.250 --> 01:57.549
It's almost 7:30.

02:01.288 --> 02:04.423
Grandma Huang:
[ Giggling ]

02:04.425 --> 02:07.192
Evan?

02:08.062 --> 02:09.628
Oh, sorry.

02:13.567 --> 02:16.602
I thought she was just making
homemade tea bags again.

02:16.604 --> 02:18.470
But I guess
she's so private,

02:18.472 --> 02:20.606
there's no way
i could have known.

02:20.608 --> 02:23.408
We heard about Charles.
We're so sorry.

02:23.410 --> 02:26.578
I always enjoyed his opinions
on local politics.

02:26.580 --> 02:27.746
What is happening?

02:35.122 --> 02:36.255
Emery...

02:40.594 --> 02:42.628
¶¶

02:42.630 --> 02:43.962
I have big news.

02:43.964 --> 02:45.631
You found the stray dog
that gets into our freezer?

02:45.633 --> 02:46.765
'Cause I'll adopt him.

02:46.767 --> 02:48.200
There's no way your mom
signs off on that.

02:48.202 --> 02:50.102
She will too.
She's mellowing out.

02:50.104 --> 02:51.870
-Do you remember the --
-no, it's not about the dog.

02:51.872 --> 02:53.438
It is news
that will affect

02:53.440 --> 02:55.340
each and every one of you
profoundly.

02:55.342 --> 02:58.644
[ Telephone rings ]

02:58.646 --> 03:01.847
Cattleman's ranch.

03:01.849 --> 03:04.616
Oh, my God.

03:10.658 --> 03:12.191
[ Door opens ]

03:12.193 --> 03:13.692
I came
as soon as I could!

03:13.694 --> 03:16.562
Eddie's first school dance.
How can I help? What can I do?

03:16.564 --> 03:18.964
Well, I went into great detail
about it on the phone.

03:18.966 --> 03:20.299
How much did you hear?

03:20.301 --> 03:22.701
Uh, "the 7th grade dance
is coming up..."

03:22.703 --> 03:24.503
And then here I am.

03:24.505 --> 03:27.372
As the principal of
a middle school, I'm very busy.

03:28.242 --> 03:31.810
But I guess I can make some time
to go over it again.

03:32.746 --> 03:33.745
[ Intercom beeps ]

03:33.747 --> 03:35.747
Shauna, push my 12:30.

03:35.749 --> 03:37.316
Shauna:
You mean when you said

03:37.318 --> 03:39.651
we'd go try
that new fro-yo place?

03:40.821 --> 03:43.488
[ Intercom beeps ]
Yes, push that.

03:43.490 --> 03:45.257
So, we're asking parents
if they can help out

03:45.259 --> 03:48.260
at the fall ball
by donating food or chaperoning.

03:48.262 --> 03:51.096
"The fall ball."
What a beautiful name.

03:51.098 --> 03:53.999
Eddie's first dance is something
I've looked forward to

03:54.001 --> 03:56.001
ever since
i moved to this country.

03:56.003 --> 03:57.536
How do you know
about American dances?

03:57.538 --> 04:00.205
You grew up in...
Taiwan?

04:00.207 --> 04:02.007
-Yes, Taiwan.
-Taiwan.

04:02.009 --> 04:04.276
Well, you know
those plastic tables they have

04:04.278 --> 04:05.510
in the center
of the pizzas?

04:05.512 --> 04:07.379
Yes, they keep the lid
off the cheese. Go on.

04:07.381 --> 04:09.948
Well, I used to work
in a factory that made those.

04:09.950 --> 04:11.116
To keep morale up,

04:11.118 --> 04:13.685
they would play John Hughes
movies on the vcr.

04:13.687 --> 04:16.855
"Pretty in pink"
over and over again.

04:16.857 --> 04:18.690
Why does she wear
so much pink?

04:18.692 --> 04:22.527
[ Scoffs ] They haven't
explained that yet, chau.

04:22.529 --> 04:24.963
They should call this movie
"sad redhead goes to the dance".

04:24.965 --> 04:26.031
Okay, chau.

04:26.033 --> 04:29.201
Wow,
Taiwan sounds rough.

04:29.203 --> 04:31.203
That wasn't in Taiwan.
That was in New Jersey.

04:31.205 --> 04:32.971
I drove through
New Jersey once.

04:32.973 --> 04:35.707
I must have watched that movie
100 times.

04:35.709 --> 04:38.744
I thought it would be
as close as I ever got
to an American dance.

04:38.746 --> 04:41.213
But now I get to experience it
through my son.

04:42.216 --> 04:44.616
All right,
I've been eavesdropping,

04:44.618 --> 04:47.052
and this is not worth
missing frozen yogurt for.

04:47.054 --> 04:48.120
Let's go.

04:50.391 --> 04:51.556
[ Video games noises ]

04:51.558 --> 04:53.825
I heard the great news.
I know!

04:53.827 --> 04:56.061
Trent just got the "game genie"
for super Nintendo.

04:56.063 --> 04:57.763
Trent: We're using it
with "Shaq fu."

04:57.765 --> 04:59.898
You type in a code, and instead
of him throwing wind,

04:59.900 --> 05:01.233
he throws
basketball jerseys.

05:01.235 --> 05:03.935
It's still terrible, but
a different kind of terrible.

05:03.937 --> 05:06.638
No. The great news
about the fall ball!

05:06.640 --> 05:08.006
Wait, what?

05:08.008 --> 05:10.108
You don't care
about my school activities.

05:10.110 --> 05:11.610
Where was this
when I needed help

05:11.612 --> 05:13.345
on my vegetable garden
for the homeless?

05:13.347 --> 05:14.913
Those were hobo melons.

05:14.915 --> 05:16.982
This is different.
This actually matters.

05:16.984 --> 05:18.283
So you're all going,
right?

05:18.285 --> 05:20.452
Yeah, we were gonna
roll through.
Sure.

05:20.454 --> 05:21.520
Sounds good.
Sounds good.

05:21.522 --> 05:22.954
Stop copying me, Dave.

05:22.956 --> 05:24.423
"Roll through"?

05:24.425 --> 05:27.259
I didn't come to this country
for my son to --

05:27.261 --> 05:29.361
you know what?
I'll take a beat.

05:30.164 --> 05:32.931
Take it easy, dad.
It's just a dance.

05:32.933 --> 05:34.366
It's not a big deal.

05:34.368 --> 05:36.001
It is a big deal.

05:36.003 --> 05:38.103
This is
a coming-of-age moment.

05:38.105 --> 05:39.971
You need to think about
what you're gonna wear,

05:39.973 --> 05:41.106
what you're gonna say,

05:41.108 --> 05:42.507
how you're gonna slow dance
with girls.

05:42.509 --> 05:44.476
Slow dance?
We got that covered.

05:44.478 --> 05:46.778
We've been watching
"the grind" on mtv.

05:46.780 --> 05:48.680
We're working on
a signature move.

05:49.683 --> 05:51.450
Oh, well,
see, that's great.

05:51.452 --> 05:52.818
[ Chuckles ]

05:52.820 --> 05:54.953
I thought you guys
weren't taking it seriously.

05:54.955 --> 05:55.954
Show me what you got.

05:55.956 --> 05:56.855
-Cool.
-Sure.

05:56.857 --> 05:58.657
No problem.
No problem.

05:58.659 --> 06:01.560
Dave, you do that again,
and you're gonna get a punch.

06:01.562 --> 06:03.695
Hit it, Walter.

06:05.632 --> 06:08.967
¶ Mr. boombastic ¶

06:08.969 --> 06:10.369
¶ what you want
is some boombastic ¶

06:10.371 --> 06:12.804
¶ romantic fantastic lover ¶

06:12.806 --> 06:14.039
¶ shaggy ¶

06:15.042 --> 06:17.142
¶ she call me Mr. boombastic ¶

06:17.144 --> 06:18.543
¶ say me fantastic ¶

06:18.545 --> 06:21.913
¶ touch me on me back,
she says I'm Mr. ro... ¶

06:21.915 --> 06:24.182
¶ mantic,
call me fantastic ¶

06:24.184 --> 06:25.984
¶ touch me on me back,
she says I'm Mr. ro... ¶

06:25.986 --> 06:27.152
shaggy!

06:27.154 --> 06:28.420
¶ ...smooth ¶

06:32.493 --> 06:34.659
¶ fantastic, touch me on me
back, she says I'm Mr. ro... ¶

06:34.661 --> 06:36.228
¶ smoo-- ¶

06:37.731 --> 06:40.832
no girl is gonna want to dance
with you if you're doing that.

06:40.834 --> 06:42.067
Yeah, they will.

06:42.069 --> 06:44.603
'Cause we're gonna gyrate them
into our orbit.

06:44.605 --> 06:47.639
[ R&B music plays ]

06:50.277 --> 06:53.678
I don't know where I'm going,
but I like it!

06:59.586 --> 07:01.086
Uh, nope.

07:02.689 --> 07:05.056
I think we're gonna need to
take a step back here.

07:05.058 --> 07:08.026
Have any of you ever had
physical contact with a girl?

07:08.028 --> 07:09.561
Yeah. Kathy.

07:09.563 --> 07:11.696
Your 2-month-old cousin
doesn't count.

07:11.698 --> 07:13.698
I fed her some peas.
So, what you're gonna do?

07:13.700 --> 07:16.101
You're gonna go to the dance
and feed girls peas?

07:16.103 --> 07:17.736
I heard Alison
is allergic to peas.

07:17.738 --> 07:18.770
Who's Alison?

07:18.772 --> 07:19.938
A girl Eddie likes.

07:19.940 --> 07:22.374
She sends her used pogs
to Africa.

07:22.376 --> 07:23.375
She's classy.

07:23.377 --> 07:25.043
Oh, great.
That's perfect.

07:25.045 --> 07:27.746
So, I assume Alison
will be at the dance.

07:27.748 --> 07:29.281
And a classy girl
like that

07:29.283 --> 07:31.716
is going to want you
to sweep her off her feet.

07:31.718 --> 07:32.717
What do you mean?

07:32.719 --> 07:35.253
[ Chuckles ]
The surprise dip.

07:35.255 --> 07:37.155
My father taught me this.

07:37.157 --> 07:39.958
He meant it as a fighting move,
but I repurposed it.

07:39.960 --> 07:42.394
Whoa.
That's pretty cool.

07:42.396 --> 07:43.829
What else can you show us,
Louis?

07:44.731 --> 07:46.598
Mr. Huang.

07:46.600 --> 07:47.732
Hmm.

07:47.734 --> 07:49.134
I can show you guys a lot.

07:49.136 --> 07:50.502
Now, if you listen to me,

07:50.504 --> 07:52.838
I promise
you'll have a great fall ball.

07:53.941 --> 07:54.906
Shaggy!

07:54.908 --> 07:56.174
Please stop that.

07:57.744 --> 08:00.846
So, I am gonna help Eddie
and his friends

08:00.848 --> 08:02.614
have a great fall ball.

08:02.616 --> 08:04.583
We need to talk about
your mother.

08:04.585 --> 08:06.184
Oh, I know.
Poor Charles.

08:06.186 --> 08:08.320
I still can't believe
he died.

08:08.322 --> 08:10.322
What?
You knew about Charles, too?

08:10.324 --> 08:12.858
Yeah, he and ma ate
at the restaurant all the time.

08:12.860 --> 08:15.527
He was the reason I put
a sneeze guard on the salad bar.

08:15.529 --> 08:17.429
Charles: Achoo!

08:17.431 --> 08:20.765
Well, did you know that he left
your mother some money?

08:20.767 --> 08:22.601
No, but that sounds like
Charles.

08:22.603 --> 08:23.702
He was very generous.

08:23.704 --> 08:26.037
He once tipped Mitch $20
on a soup.

08:26.039 --> 08:27.172
Mitch ran to the store

08:27.174 --> 08:29.107
and brought back a Jackson's
worth of candy.

08:29.109 --> 08:30.675
[ Laughs ]
What a night that was.

08:30.677 --> 08:32.844
We were flying, boy!
Louis.

08:32.846 --> 08:35.447
[ Sighs ] You know she's
just gonna put all that money

08:35.449 --> 08:36.882
under her mattress.

08:36.884 --> 08:40.051
Instead, she should invest it
with me on a house to flip.

08:40.053 --> 08:42.787
A great colonial
just came on the market.

08:42.789 --> 08:44.055
That's a good idea.

08:44.057 --> 08:46.358
Great.
So you'll ask her for me.

08:46.360 --> 08:48.627
Well, you know what will happen
if I do that.

08:48.629 --> 08:50.795
She'll just ask<i> me</i>
why<i> you</i> didn't ask her

08:50.797 --> 08:52.731
and the Gulf between you
will grow.

08:52.733 --> 08:53.965
Oh, I can't ask her.

08:53.967 --> 08:56.134
We have
such a chilly relationship.

08:56.136 --> 08:58.169
Well, that doesn't have to be
the case.

08:58.171 --> 09:00.205
Spend some time with her,
warm her up.

09:00.207 --> 09:02.307
And when the time is right,
ask her.

09:07.047 --> 09:08.980
Do you think
the time was right for that?

09:08.982 --> 09:10.982
I do not.

09:12.519 --> 09:13.752
Sajak:<i> Up to $1,200.</i>

09:13.754 --> 09:16.521
[<i> Applause</i> ]

09:16.523 --> 09:17.889
Hi, mom.

09:17.891 --> 09:18.990
What are you watching?

09:18.992 --> 09:20.292
"Wheel."

09:23.263 --> 09:24.996
So, I was thinking,

09:24.998 --> 09:27.499
would you
like to go out for lunch today?

09:27.501 --> 09:28.667
My treat.

09:28.669 --> 09:29.834
[ Speaking Chinese ]

09:29.836 --> 09:31.736
Right.

09:31.738 --> 09:35.807
Okay, well, what about we do
something after lunch?

09:37.044 --> 09:40.211
Wow, so busy
all of a sudden.

09:40.213 --> 09:42.847
These aren't the droids
you're looking for.

09:42.849 --> 09:45.016
What?

09:45.018 --> 09:48.186
[<i> Applause</i> ]

09:48.188 --> 09:49.688
Oh.

09:49.690 --> 09:51.856
Well,
i have nothing going on.

09:51.858 --> 09:54.993
Mind if I tag along with you
on your busy day?

09:58.198 --> 10:01.266
I want a new jetta.

10:04.571 --> 10:06.705
[ Speaking Chinese ]

10:11.411 --> 10:13.712
You take coins
out of the fountain?

10:18.318 --> 10:21.219
Let me just push away these
mosquitos having sex,

10:21.221 --> 10:23.355
and I'll stick my arm in.

10:31.832 --> 10:32.964
Ah.

10:37.904 --> 10:39.404
Speaking of a good find,

10:39.406 --> 10:42.273
there's this house
that just went on the market.

10:42.275 --> 10:44.509
If you invested
your inheritance with me,

10:44.511 --> 10:45.977
I could double your money.

10:54.521 --> 10:58.256
Okay, so if I have one takeaway
from John Hughes movies,

10:58.258 --> 11:00.458
it's that dressing confidently
matters.

11:00.460 --> 11:01.860
Drop some knowledge on me,
dad.

11:01.862 --> 11:03.361
I want to look fly
at the dance.

11:03.363 --> 11:04.663
Show me
what you feel best in.

11:07.100 --> 11:08.500
Why?

11:08.502 --> 11:10.835
Why does this make you
feel confident?

11:10.837 --> 11:14.005
Because it's the perfect mix
of class and street.

11:14.007 --> 11:15.206
Kind of like Alison.

11:15.208 --> 11:16.875
I get it now,
and I love it.

11:16.877 --> 11:18.009
You do?

11:18.011 --> 11:19.778
No, but if you're confident
in it,

11:19.780 --> 11:21.346
then I feel confident
in you.

11:21.348 --> 11:24.115
I mean, look at steff and blane
in "pretty in pink".

11:24.117 --> 11:26.317
They wore blazers
with rolled-up sleeves

11:26.319 --> 11:29.454
like female stand-up comics,
and they were the popular kids.

11:29.456 --> 11:31.623
I don't know who that is,
but thanks.

11:31.625 --> 11:34.926
Okay,
so your walls are good.

11:36.029 --> 11:37.996
Now we need to work
on your roof.

11:37.998 --> 11:40.031
Buck, this is sick.

11:40.033 --> 11:41.966
¶ Yeah ¶

11:41.968 --> 11:44.969
I don't think that means
what you think it means.

11:44.971 --> 11:46.705
Yeah, it does.
'Cause I'm money.

11:46.707 --> 11:50.375
[ Chuckles ] Hey, like I said,
if you feel good, I feel good.

11:54.347 --> 11:55.814
Okay, Lou, so five cuts?

11:55.816 --> 11:57.248
Uh, no,
just for my boy.

11:57.250 --> 11:59.818
But I got frosted tips.

11:59.820 --> 12:01.319
[ Sighs ]

12:01.321 --> 12:03.988
All right, buck, what's
the damage for the tips?

12:03.990 --> 12:05.323
You're not gonna like it.

12:05.325 --> 12:07.258
He asked
for the premium tinfoil.

12:07.260 --> 12:10.061
[ Cash register beeping ]

12:11.832 --> 12:15.233
¶¶

12:17.437 --> 12:19.337
you must have
a huge pair of rocks

12:19.339 --> 12:20.939
to show up
looking like that.

12:20.941 --> 12:23.508
Okay, I've got to head to
the dance early to set up food.

12:23.510 --> 12:27.011
So Walter's dad, Walter sr.,
will be giving you all a ride.

12:27.013 --> 12:29.347
Hey, you got a sec?

12:29.349 --> 12:32.217
Son, I want to talk to you
about something serious.

12:32.219 --> 12:34.185
Things could
get heated tonight.

12:34.187 --> 12:37.122
You're having fun with your
girl, lost in the moment,

12:37.124 --> 12:39.190
you won't want to stop
to think about protection.

12:39.192 --> 12:40.291
What?!

12:40.293 --> 12:42.393
Take this with you,
and in the moment,

12:42.395 --> 12:46.231
please, please make
the smart choice and use it.

12:46.233 --> 12:48.933
That's mitchum.
That's the good stuff.

12:48.935 --> 12:50.034
[ Exhales deeply ]

12:50.036 --> 12:52.036
don't worry, dad.
I got it covered.

12:52.038 --> 12:55.039
We all went in
on a bottle of Polo Cologne.

12:55.041 --> 12:56.241
Hmm.

12:56.243 --> 12:59.043
We did the math.
We get three sprays each.

12:59.045 --> 13:03.548
Check it --
two cheeks and a valley.

13:03.550 --> 13:06.084
[ Chuckles ]
Eddie, I'm so excited for you.

13:06.086 --> 13:08.887
These are the critical hours
leading up to the big dance.

13:08.889 --> 13:11.623
In the movie, this is when Andie
assembled her own dress.

13:11.625 --> 13:12.724
Right.

13:12.726 --> 13:14.092
Well, I'm excited, too.

13:14.094 --> 13:16.895
This is the first time I'm gonna
see Alison outside of school.

13:16.897 --> 13:18.763
What's your plan
when you see her?

13:18.765 --> 13:20.064
I don't know.

13:20.066 --> 13:22.400
